Prices of gold peaked on Aug 6.
They also topped the US$2,000 mark for the first time in history on Aug 4. 1,700 1,600 1,500 Mr Francis Tan, investment strategist at UOB Private Bank. 1,400 Jan Feb March April Aug Sept Oct Nov Dec TYPES OF GOLD INVESTMENT Investment­s: 55.4% Gold bullion:
Physical gold of high purity that is often stored as bars, ingots or coins. Gold futures contract:
Parties agree for the buyer to purchase the commodity at a fixed quantity and time in the future. Gold exchange-traded funds (ETFs):
For investors who want to have a stake in the gold market without investing in the physical commodity itself. GOLD EXPORTS $700 million In the first nine months of this year, Singapore’s non-monetary gold exports grew by $700 million on average per month, compared with the same period in 2019. WHY IS GOLD A SAFE-HAVEN ASSET? Gold offers more certainty and therefore glitters more. Past experience also shows that gold prices shoot up during an economic crisis because of the heightened demand, making it a self-fulfilling prophecy and a safe haven. 12.1 TONNES Central banks sold gold for the first time in a decade, seizing high prices as a chance to soften the impact of Covid-19. 1.1KG Amount of gold Apple estimated in 2019 that its recycling robot Daisy could recover from every 100,000 iPhone devices. GOLD PRICES SOAR AMID PANDEMIC
Gold spot prices hit an all-time high due to strong demand. This refers to the price at which gold can be bought or sold for immediate delivery. May June July WHAT IS GOLD USED FOR? The global demand for gold was 892.2 tonnes in the third quarter of this year. This was an increase from the 36.9 per cent used for investment­s in the same period last year. Technology: 8.6% Jewellery: 37.3% NOTE: Figures do not add up to 100% due to rounding up. STOCKING UP ON GOLD Central banks stock up on the yellow metal to boost the economy and hedge against economic uncertaint­y, inflation and currency devaluatio­ns. US$211.7 million (S$282 million): Singapore’s gold reserves as at October. 4.1 million troy ounces (127.5 tonnes): Amount of gold in Singapore’s reserves. LEADING GOLD EXPORTING COUNTRIES WORLDWIDE IN 2019 US$ billion GOLD RESERVES OF LARGEST GOLD HOLDING COUNTRIES WORLDWIDE AS OF SEPTEMBER 2020 Switzerlan­d 62 Hong Kong 25.2 tonnes Switzerlan­d has four of the world’s largest gold refineries. United Kingdom 23.3 United States 8,133.53 United Arab Emirates 17.7 Germany 3,362.47 United States 17.2 Italy 2,451.86 Australia 16.2 France 2,436.12 Singapore does not have gold mines but it is home to gold refineries and bullion product manufactur­ing plants. Gold is also stored at Le Freeport, a secured logistics hub in Changi North Crescent. Canada 15.3 Russia 2, 298.67 Singapore 11.6 China 1,948.32 Thailand 7.6 Switzerlan­d 1,040.01 Peru 6.7 Japan 765.22 Germany 6.6 Turkey 691.01 Japan 6.4 India 668.25 0 2,000 4,000 6,000 8,000 10,000 0 10 20 30 40 50 60 70 Sources: BLOOMBERG, STATISTA, MONETARY AUTHORIT Y OF SINGAPORE, ENTERPRISE SINGAPORE, SGX, APPLE ENVIRONMEN­TAL RESPONSIBI­LIT Y REPORT 2019 PHOTO: REUTERS STRAITS TIMES GRAPHICS • • •
